    "body": "Problem:\n\nWhen using prompt_appendbuf with multi-element list,\nthe first item is concated and rest replace the prompt instead of\ninserting the lines before the prompt.\n\nSolution:\n\nConcat first element with replace_buf and insert the rest of the list\nwith set_buffer_lines.\n\nThe tests that were added do not pass before this change and clearly\nshow the issue.\n\nSigned-off-by: Tomas Slusny <slusnucky@gmail.com>\n",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "_links": {
                "html": {
                    "href": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/39550#discussion_r3213404526"
                },
                "pull_request": {
                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/pulls/39550"
                },
                "self": {
                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/pulls/comments/3213404526"
                }
            },
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "You can simplify this quite a bit. `did_concat` can only be true when lines is a list. so the var_list check is redundant. You can avoid all the list building stuff. Just take the first item from the list replace the line then remove first item from the list and append rest of the list.\r\n\r\n```patch\r\ndiff --git a/src/nvim/eval/buffer.c b/src/nvim/eval/buffer.c\r\nindex 8fb6920e04..0583c62102 100644\r\n--- a/src/nvim/eval/buffer.c\r\n+++ b/src/nvim/eval/buffer.c\r\n@@ -317,26 +317,16 @@ void f_prompt_appendbuf(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv, EvalFuncData fptr)\r\n   }\r\n \r\n   if (did_emsg == did_emsg_before) {\r\n-    if (did_concat && lines->v_type == VAR_LIST && tv_list_len(lines->vval.v_list) > 1) {\r\n+    if (did_concat && tv_list_len(lines->vval.v_list) > 1) {\r\n       // Multi-element list with concat: first element (already concatenated)\r\n       // replaces the line at lnum, remaining elements are inserted after.\r\n       list_T *l = lines->vval.v_list;\r\n       listitem_T *li = tv_list_first(l);\r\n-      typval_T first_tv = TV_INITIAL_VALUE;\r\n-      first_tv.v_type = VAR_STRING;\r\n-      first_tv.vval.v_string = (char *)tv_get_string(&li->li_tv);\r\n-      set_buffer_lines(buf, lnum, false, &first_tv, rettv);\r\n+      set_buffer_lines(buf, lnum, false, &li->li_tv, rettv);\r\n \r\n       if (rettv->vval.v_number == 0) {\r\n-        list_T *rest = tv_list_alloc(kListLenMayKnow);\r\n-        for (listitem_T *li2 = li->li_next; li2 != NULL; li2 = li2->li_next) {\r\n-          tv_list_append_string(rest, tv_get_string(&li2->li_tv), -1);\r\n-        }\r\n-        typval_T rest_tv = TV_INITIAL_VALUE;\r\n-        rest_tv.v_type = VAR_LIST;\r\n-        rest_tv.vval.v_list = rest;\r\n-        set_buffer_lines(buf, lnum, true, &rest_tv, rettv);\r\n-        tv_list_unref(rest);\r\n+        tv_list_item_remove(l, li);\r\n+        set_buffer_lines(buf, lnum, true, lines, rettv);\r\n       }\r\n     } else {\r\n       set_buffer_lines(buf, lnum, buf->b_prompt_append_new_line, lines, rettv);\r\n```",
            "commit_id": "b9dc399646b42a880eb0630576a430992bfa0b10",
            "created_at": "2026-05-09T16:07:15Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -314,7 +317,30 @@ void f_prompt_appendbuf(typval_T *argvars, typval_T *rettv, EvalFuncData fptr)\n   }\n \n   if (did_emsg == did_emsg_before) {\n-    set_buffer_lines(buf, lnum, buf->b_prompt_append_new_line, lines, rettv);\n+    if (did_concat && lines->v_type == VAR_LIST && tv_list_len(lines->vval.v_list) > 1) {",
