        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> please have patience, and keep PRs rebased to avoid going stale :)\r\n> \r\n> <img alt=\"image\" width=\"496\" height=\"295\" src=\"https://private-user-images.githubusercontent.com/1359421/589671413-0af7d981-33af-46d4-b497-8b2143e4c9d5.png?jwt=eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9..Ou1FzMYXxwRVx--Ys4iao8bKbArjUgggokBzGgYMpgI\">\r\n\r\nAh sorry, got a bit impatient as i was juggling 2 branches because of this on one of my repos :d yea im keeping the PR rebased locally as im using it but did not wanted to spam force push and keep triggering the builds, but i will keep that in mind. \r\n\r\nI can explain the change, so the issue is that with the original set buf lines call, if we are in replace mode, it replaces everything in the line range.\r\n\r\nBut we need to be in replace mode for set lines because the first entry in the appendbuf list is being concated with existing line, but the rest of lines need to be appended. So this PR simply splits the logic in 2, first it uses replace mode for first entry in list, and append mode for rest of the lines. Without this change it stayed in replace mode for all lines so it also replaced user prompt, and that broke next appendbuf calls as well as the user prompt got replaced.",
